stylometry: RISKSIMTABLE allows a model to run with multiple inputs and variables, using standard deviation, and probability, and it gives you an accurate protrayal of what may happen in the real world.  An example of how it could be used in a simulation model, lets say we have three outcomes, A, B, and C, and the probablilty that any of these outcomes will occurr is 20%, 45% and 35% respectivly, and the cost for each is $1, $2, and $3 respectivly, RISKSIMTABLE will use the table you created with this data and give you outcomes based on that data, that will allow analyst to study and decide what course of action to take.
